TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,4,1);
$b = random(2,4,1);
$c = random(1,6,1);

$x1 = random(-2,-1,1);
$x2 = 0;
$x3 = random(1,2,1);

$y1 = $a*$x1*$x1 + $b*$x1 + $c;
$y2 = $c;
$y3 = $a*$x3*$x3 + $b*$x3 + $c;

BEGIN_TEXT

Find the quadratic polynomial whose graph goes through the points \( ($x1,$y1), \) \( ($x2,$y2), \) and 
\( ($x3,$y3) \). 
$BR
\(f(x)=\) \{ans_rule(7)\} \(x^2+\) \{ans_rule(7)\} \(x+\) \{ans_rule(7)\}

END_TEXT

